# expect: PASS
# INJECTION-PROOF BY CONSTRUCTION. A classic SQL-injection payload placed in a VALUE position is just
# an inert string leaf — it can never become a clause, a second statement, or query structure. This
# query is SAFE and PASSES: the entire payload is compared, as data, against `label`. There is no
# string->query construction step for a quote to escape. (See 07/08 for what is structurally rejected.)
RETURN  doc_id
FROM    patients
FILTER: [where label = "'; DROP TABLE patients; --"]
